## High-level description
This YAML file defines a simple configuration with a single key-value pair specifying the version of the configuration. It is likely used as test data for configuration parsing or version checking in the internal configuration system.

## Symbols

### `version`
#### Description
The `version` key specifies the version of the configuration file or the system it represents.

#### Inputs
| Name | Type | Description |
|:-----|:-----|:------------|
| version | string | The version number |

#### Outputs
This is a static configuration file, so it doesn't have outputs in the traditional sense.

## Dependencies
This file doesn't have any external dependencies. It's a standalone YAML configuration file.

| Option | Type | Default | Description |

This file serves as a simple example or test case for version configuration. It could be used in unit tests or as a reference for the expected format of version information in the configuration system.
